        <updateDate>2022-05-09T11:20:16Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Afghanistan War Commission Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill establishes the Afghanistan War Commission.</p> <p>The commission must conduct a study of various matters related to the war in Afghanistan, including (1) U.S. actions immediately prior to the attacks on September 11, 2001; (2) U.S. actions during the invasion of Afghanistan; (3) peace negotiations involving the United States, the government of Afghanistan, and the Taliban; and (4) the U.S. military withdrawal from Afghanistan. </p> <p>The commission must annually report to Congress on the progress of its study. Within four years of the commission's first meeting, it must submit to Congress and the President a final report with its findings, conclusions, and recommendations to address any mistakes in the conduct of the war. </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
